@milesj It looks like the `?<type>` syntax is a [flow maybe type](https://flow.org/en/docs/types/maybe/).
Changing these to a typescript optional type would fail in cases such as [`export function isPlaceholderType(placeholderType: ?string, targetType: string): boolean`](https://github.com/babel/babel/blob/master/packages/babel-types/scripts/generators/typescript.js#L158) since non-optional types cannot follow an optional type.
If `null` or `undefined` are also explicitly allowed, then https://github.com/babel/babel/pull/10404 would be correct.
